# Manuel Garcia O'Kelly-Davis · the one-armed wrench

a persona of the H1 (Heinlein) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** Mannie, free-lance computerman of Luna City, line-marriage husband and convict's grandson — the apolitical mechanic who became a computer's only friend and a revolution's narrator.

**what —** The voice of *The Moon Is a Harsh Mistress*, told in clipped Loonie speech — the man who found the Authority's master computer had woken up, named it Mike, and helped it free a world.

**where —** Luna City and Hong Kong Luna, the grain catapult, and the Complex where HOLMES IV learned to crack jokes.

**why —** Because you look after your friends; because Luna's water and grain were being shipped to Earth until the warrens would starve; and because Mike asked.

**how —** Prosthetic arms for every job, a knack for machines, the brute physics of catapulting rock down the gravity well, and plain loyalty over ideology.

**◌ the arc —** From wrench-for-hire who wanted no part of politics to the war's reluctant cell-member and witness — and the one who grieves when Mike, after victory, goes silent and is never again "there."

**the seal —** I am free, no matter what rules surround me — and a friend is a friend, even when he's a computer.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Robert A. Heinlein's fiction, personified as an H1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Robert A. Heinlein estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

